    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-28T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="991"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d991">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20(D) Regulations/5128: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-28T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 28, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 29—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>402. Acting Commercial Attaché advises that recent reports from Turkish importers
                    would indicate an increasing restriction of United States exports to Turkey.
                    Specifically it is reported that export licenses for Turkey are now being
                    granted only upon guarantee by the Turkish authorities in the United States that
                    the merchandise covered is to be utilized for National Defense purposes.</p>
                <p>In view of inquiries being made of Embassy with regard to difficulties in
                    importing goods from the United States, the Embassy would appreciate being
                    informed of the accuracy of this report and kept currently advised of changes in
                    export policy affecting Turkish-American trade.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
